But the country which lies between these two mountainous places, is called the Great plain (Μέγα πεδίον), extended from the village Ginnaber to the lake Asphaltites, in length a thousand two hundred fur- longs” (a hundred and fifty miles), “in breadth, a hundred and twenty furlongs” (fifteen miles); and Jordan cuts it in the middle.''
